title.en: Workshop - European Digital Credentials for Learning

description.en: The Directorate B deep dive series was kicked-off with a session dedicated to the European Digital Credentials for Learning (EDC). The session included a presentation of the EDC infrastructure and of the developments in digital credentialing in the skills field. The presentation also covered the different synergies between the work on digital credentials and other EU initiatives (EU Student Card Initiative, Single Digital Gateway, EU digital identity), and included a short demo of the tools that can be used to build, issue and view EDCs.

title.en: Workshop A3: Unique academic e-course for career practitioners on mobility in Europe

description.en: Jointly developed by Estonian EUROPASS, EUROGUIDANCE AND EURES quality labelled e-course as a powerful tool for enhancing practitioners 'skills and competences in multiculturalism and learning and working mobility in EU'. Career practitioners are more often faced with mobility related requests in times of globalisation, digitalisation and demographic changes. Participants of the workshop could learn about the e-course which provides an opportunity: (*) to expand understanding related to international mobility and multiculturalism; and (*) to gain knowledge for working with people who want to go to study or work abroad, and who have come to Estonia from abroad and need further career guidance. During the interactive session practical exercises were shared. 2021's e-course Multiculturalism,                                learning and work mobility in the context of career development was recognised by Estonian Quality Agency for Education as worthy of the quality label.

title.en: Workshop A3: Unique academic e-course for career practitioners on mobility in Europe
Workshop A2: Go online! What can European Solidarity Corps General Online Training bring to our networks?

description.en: General Online Training (GOT) is a web platform offered by European Commission that provides various learning modules for European Solidarity Corps participants, but also for young people who are not participants yet, but want to find out about opportunities for mobility abroad, learn about EUs fundamental values, find practical tips for international mobility etc. In this workshop participants explored hands-on what GOT has to offer and talk about possible synergies with all the networks.

title.en: Workshop A2: Go online! What can European Solidarity Corps General Online Training bring to our networks?
Workshop A1: How to reach vulnerable people for life long guidance?

description.en: This session focused on sharing the main findings of the moderators' exploration on this topic. They conducted a literature review and interviewed experts in five European countries who work on guidance policy on labor market or in a more operational role. Currently they are exploring the situation in the Netherlands and we will tell participants what they will have found out at that time. After this short presentation the participants of the different countries were invited to share their good practices on this issue and make it visible for all participants of the conference.
